explanation: This solution uses a rejection sampling approach to generate a random number in the range [1, 10]. It repeatedly generates two random numbers in the range [1, 7] and combines them to form a number in the range [1, 49]. If the generated number is in the range [1, 40], it is rejected and the process is repeated. The final number is then reduced modulo 10 to generate a random number in the range [1, 10]. This approach ensures that the generated numbers are uniformly distributed and has a high efficiency.

